The paper deals with epistemic reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves modeling and solving reasoning problems, which can be related to logic and computation (cs.LO). The scenario described in the paper involves a robotic wheelchair navigating autonomously, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of functional fluents and static causal laws suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and analysis, which can be related to machine learning (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY).
